<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-03-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-03-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="231" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d231">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 811.001/208: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                                <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss></hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><hi rend="smallcaps">On Board <placeName>U.
                                    S. S. “George Washington</placeName></hi>,” <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-03-12">March 12,
                            1919</date>.<lb/>[Received 10:20 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                    <p>For Colonel House. Shall probably reach Brest at 8:30 and shall of course
                        take dinner on the boat before going ashore. Regret late arrival but in
                        circumstances of course agree to arrangements suggested.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>